<dl id="n12009e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12009e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12009e"> 9(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Gen Estienne forbids use / of word &lsquo;tank&rsquo;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Enfin, le gouvernement pourrait agir tr&egrave;s utilement. Pendant la guerre, un ordre du g&eacute;n&eacute;ral Estienne a suffi &agrave; proscrire le mot <i>tank</i> et &agrave; le remplacer par <i>char d&apos;assaut</i>. <br><font color="green">[Also, the government could act in a useful way. During the war <mark>a single order of General Estienne was enough to prohibit the word <i>tank</i></mark> and to replace it by <i>char d&apos;assaut</i>.]</font> <small> Jacques Boulenger &amp; Andr&eacute; Th&eacute;rive, <a name="SOIR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SOIR"><cite title="source">Les Soir&eacute;es du Grammaire-Club</cite></a> (1924) 140</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
